5:
We've finally arrived. The castle
appears even more impressive up
close.
8:
Definitely a lot bigger than I thought
it'd be, and more than enough room
for one princess.
11:
You sure we can just waltz right in?
Feels kinda wrong somehow...
16:
What is there to worry about? It is
not as if we are here to cause
trouble! Let us tarry no longer!
27: GAAH! What is the meaning of this?!
31:
What are you standing out here for?
Don't you think you've neglected me
for long enough?!
34:
I'm going to be sick if I have to
spend another day eating steamed
potatoes!
38:
Potatoes?! I'm the one that will be
sick if you keep shaking me around!
Unhand me this instant!
42:
...Grey, since when did you have soft
and smooth skin?
47: Who in the world are you people?!
52:
Good day. I'm Stella. Are you
perhaps Prika?
60:
Y-yeah? Can't you tell just by
looking at us?
65:
That means you came from outside!
Have you met with Grey?
70:
You must have run into him on your
way in! Didn't you see anyone with
white hair and wrinkles?
73:
Uh, nope, can't say we have. The
only person we ran into doesn't
meet that description.
82:
Oh, you're ALL people, including that
fluffy, furry thing, right?
86:
That means you're guests, and I
should be rolling out the red carpet!
Come inside!
90:
What an odd young lady... Is she
truly a member of royalty?
94:
I guess? Looks that way to me, at
least.
102:
Ahem. I knew this day would come
eventually, so I've had preparations
always at the ready!
104:
Go on, dig in! Help yourself to
everything on the table!
108:
Are these all potatoes? I almost feel
like eating so many will turn my
taste buds into sand...
110:
Sand? Don't be ridiculous! It's not as
if you're one of the buildings in town!
113:
Speaking of which, you didn't touch
any of them, did you?
118:
Err, one of us might've laid a hand
on stuff without knowing it was
gonna disintegrate...
123:
I have to rebuild AGAIN? Oh gosh, I
can feel a headache coming on...
127:
Wow... So you actually built
everything by yourself using magic.
129:
But why do it in this forest? There's
practically no one living here.
133:
Well, I needed space to build a town
and castle. How else am I going to
properly welcome my Prince
Charming?
135:
I have to be ready whenever he
finally shows up. That's what Grey
told me, anyway.
139:
Huh... Kind of a weird thing to make
someone prepare for...
146:
Did somebody say "prince"?
Fortunately for you, the genuine
article is already in your midst. I am
Razelt, a prince of the Farlands!
151: The Farlands? Never heard of it.
154:
Besides, I'm not waiting for just any
prince. I've been exchanging letters
with Prince Frau of Mosnia!
157:
The audacity of this woman! Wait,
did you say Mosnia? But...
162:
You mentioned coming here to do
an investigation or something.
164:
That means running around and
researching things, doesn't it?
168:
You all seem a little young to be
exploring outside. Actually, I don't
think I've ever met people as young
as you before!
173:
W-would you mind composing
yourself and speaking a tad bit
slower?
178:
Well, excuuuse me for being a little
excited! This is the first time I've
spoken with people outside of Grey!
183:
Prika, have you lived here your entire
life?
187:
Yes, I've never gone beyond the
walls. It's too dangerous outside.
191:
It's okay to be a little cautious, but...
You've honestly never gone outside
a SINGLE time?
195:
Grey insisted against it! What else
was I supposed to do?
198: What? Did I say something weird?
206:
It came from beyond the castle
walls. Are those insolent poppets
wreaking havoc again?
213:
Why are the poppets acting on their
own?!
216: I command you to obey me!
221:
A-are you out of your mind! That
was dangerous!
225:
I don't understand! Why aren't they
listening to me?
